</LIST>
<LIST><PARAGRAPH>Specify the system that you want to access:</PARAGRAPH>
<BULLETLISTIND><BULLETIND><PARAGRAPH>Click on the <SCREENDISPLAY>Local System</SCREENDISPLAY> radio button to connect to the local host (the system on which you started Embedded Support Partner). (Refer to <XREF IDREF="15055" TYPE="GRAPHIC">Figure&nbsp;7-9</XREF>.)</PARAGRAPH>
</BULLETIND>
<BULLETIND><PARAGRAPH>Click on the <SCREENDISPLAY>Remote System</SCREENDISPLAY> radio button to connect to a remote system. Enter the name of the system or IP address of the system in the field. (Refer to <XREF IDREF="12412" TYPE="GRAPHIC">Figure&nbsp;7-10</XREF>.)</PARAGRAPH>
<PARAGRAPH><FIGURE><GRAPHIC FILE="starting-006.gif" POSITION="INLINE" SCALE="FALSE"><CAPTION LBL="7-9"><PREFIX>Figure 7-9 </PREFIX><XREFTARGET ID="15055">Connecting to System Group Manager Mode on the Local System</CAPTION>
</FIGURE>
<FIGURE><GRAPHIC FILE="starting-002.gif" POSITION="INLINE" SCALE="FALSE"><CAPTION LBL="7-10"><PREFIX>Figure 7-10 </PREFIX><XREFTARGET ID="12412">Connecting to System Group Manager Mode on a Remote System</CAPTION>
